---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is Redwood Outdoors a good sauna brand?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Redwood Outdoors is one of the better premium outdoor sauna brands in the US market. Their Thermowood construction (heat-treated Scandinavian wood) outperforms standard cedar in rot and moisture resistance for outdoor installations. They are positioned above Almost Heaven in quality and price. Main downsides: higher cost and limited warranty (1 year) compared to some competitors."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does a Redwood Outdoors sauna cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Redwood Outdoors saunas range from roughly $3,500 for a standard cedar barrel to $6,600+ for their Thermowood Extra-Wide Barrel and Panorama models. The Thermowood Cabin (4-person) is their flagship and starts around $6,599. Shipping and electrical installation add $800-$2,000 to total cost."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Thermowood and why does it matter for saunas?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Thermowood is Scandinavian wood (typically spruce or pine) that has been heat-treated in a steam kiln at 185-215°C. The process drives out resins and moisture, reducing the wood's equilibrium moisture content and making it significantly more resistant to rot, insects, and dimensional warping from temperature changes. For an outdoor sauna exposed to weather year-round, Thermowood outlasts standard cedar in most climates."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Base
  title="Redwood Outdoors Sauna Review (2025): Thermowood Quality at a Premium Price"
  description="Honest Redwood Outdoors sauna review. Thermowood vs cedar, model lineup, who it's for, and how it compares to Almost Heaven. Is the premium worth it?"
  canonical="/brands/redwood-outdoors-sauna-review"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">Redwood Outdoors Sauna Review (2025)</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-500 mb-8">Updated January 2025 &mdash; Backyard Sauna Pro</p>

    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <img src="/images/lifestyle/barrel-sauna-field.jpg" alt="Redwood Outdoors barrel sauna outdoors" class="w-full object-cover max-h-80" loading="lazy" width="1200" height="800" />
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-stone-700">
      <strong>Affiliate disclosure:</strong> As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This page may contain affiliate links including links to Redwood Outdoors.
    </div>

    <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">Quick Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-stone-700 text-sm mb-3">Redwood Outdoors makes well-built outdoor saunas using Thermowood — heat-treated Scandinavian wood that genuinely outperforms standard cedar for long-term outdoor use. Their models are priced at the premium end ($3,500-$6,600+) but the material quality justifies it for buyers who want a sauna that holds up in all four seasons without regular maintenance. Not the choice for budget-first buyers. The right choice for buyers who want a permanent, high-quality installation and are willing to pay for it.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Pros</p>
          <ul class="text-stone-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Thermowood outperforms cedar outdoors</li>
            <li>Serious build quality</li>
            <li>US-based support</li>
            <li>$250 buyer coupon available</li>
            <li>Nationwide shipping</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-stone-700 mb-1">Cons</p>
          <ul class="text-stone-600 space-y-1">
            <li>Premium price point</li>
            <li>1-year warranty only</li>
            <li>Less established than Almost Heaven</li>
            <li>Fewer Amazon reviews vs AH</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">What Is Thermowood and Why Does It Matter?</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Most barrel saunas in North America use western red cedar. Cedar is a fine choice and what Almost Heaven, Dundalk, and most competitors use. Redwood Outdoors differentiates on their Thermowood models — Scandinavian spruce or pine that has been heat-treated in steam kilns at 185-215°C.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">The heat treatment drives out resins, reduces the wood's equilibrium moisture content, and restructures the cell walls so the wood absorbs and releases moisture more slowly. The result: significantly better rot resistance, less warping from seasonal temperature swings, and better long-term stability in wet climates.</p>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">In practice, a Thermowood barrel sauna requires less maintenance than cedar in climates with heavy rain or freeze-thaw cycles. If you're in the Pacific Northwest, upper Midwest, or Northeast where a cedar barrel sauna needs annual treatment to avoid greying and weathering, Thermowood's advantage compounds over time.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-6">Redwood Outdoors Model Lineup</h2>

    <div class="space-y-5 mb-10">
      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="mb-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-amber-700 bg-amber-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wide">Most Popular</span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-1">Thermowood Extra-Wide Barrel Sauna</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-3 text-sm">Their flagship barrel. Wider than a standard barrel profile — more comfortable for 2-3 adults. Compatible with wood-burning stove or electric heater. Thermowood construction throughout. This is the model that most Redwood Outdoors buyers choose. Runs approximately $6,600 before shipping.</p>
        <a href="https://www.redwoodoutdoors.com/collections/barrel-saunas" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="inline-block bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">View on Redwood Outdoors</a>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="mb-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900">Thermowood Panorama Sauna</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-3 text-sm">Their premium barrel with a large panoramic window. For buyers who want a view from the sauna — backyard, woods, or waterfront. Same Thermowood quality. Starts around $6,599. The window is a genuine differentiator if your site has a view worth preserving.</p>
        <a href="https://www.redwoodoutdoors.com/collections/barrel-saunas" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="inline-block border border-amber-400 text-amber-700 font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors">View on Redwood Outdoors</a>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="mb-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900">Thermowood Cabin Sauna (4-Person)</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-3 text-sm">Their cabin-style (square) option. 4-person capacity with electric heater. More floor space than a barrel, better for groups. Thermowood exterior, proper insulated walls. Starts around $6,599. Requires 240V. See our <a href="/guides/outdoor-sauna-ideas" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">outdoor sauna ideas guide</a> for cabin vs barrel comparison.</p>
        <a href="https://www.redwoodoutdoors.com/collections/cabin-saunas" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="inline-block border border-amber-400 text-amber-700 font-semibold px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-amber-50 transition-colors">View on Redwood Outdoors</a>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-5 bg-white">
        <div class="mb-2">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-stone-900">Cedar Barrel Saunas (Entry Level)</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-3 text-sm">Redwood Outdoors also sells standard western red cedar barrels starting around $3,500. These are in the same tier as Almost Heaven. The Thermowood models are the reason to choose Redwood Outdoors over competitors — the cedar lineup is solid but not a strong differentiator.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Redwood Outdoors vs Almost Heaven</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
      <table class="text-sm w-full">
        <thead>
          <tr class="text-left text-stone-500 border-b border-stone-200">
            <th class="pb-2 pr-6">Factor</th>
            <th class="pb-2 pr-6">Redwood Outdoors</th>
            <th class="pb-2">Almost Heaven</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-stone-700">
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Wood type</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Thermowood (heat-treated)</td>
            <td class="py-2">Western red cedar</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Entry price</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">~$3,500 (cedar), $6,600+ (Thermowood)</td>
            <td class="py-2">~$1,599 (2-person barrel)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Outdoor durability</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Excellent (Thermowood)</td>
            <td class="py-2">Good (cedar needs maintenance)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Brand history</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Newer, growing fast</td>
            <td class="py-2">30+ years, established</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-stone-100">
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Warranty</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">1 year</td>
            <td class="py-2">5 years (structural)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6 font-semibold">Best for</td>
            <td class="py-2 pr-6">Wet climates, premium buyers</td>
            <td class="py-2">Value-focused, any climate</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">Who Should Buy Redwood Outdoors</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-4">Redwood Outdoors makes sense for buyers who:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-700 mb-8 ml-4 text-sm">
      <li>Live in a wet or cold climate where outdoor wood is exposed to heavy moisture, freeze-thaw cycles, or high humidity year-round</li>
      <li>Want the best long-term outdoor durability and are willing to pay for it</li>
      <li>Value the panoramic window option or want a cabin-style sauna</li>
      <li>Have a budget above $5,000 for the full installation</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-stone-700 mb-6">Buyers who should look at Almost Heaven instead: anyone budget-limited, anyone in a dry climate where cedar performs well, and buyers who want a longer warranty.</p>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-2">Redwood Outdoors Affiliate Coupon</p>
      <p class="text-stone-700 text-sm">When you purchase through our affiliate link, you receive $250 off your Redwood Outdoors order automatically. That makes the Thermowood models meaningfully more competitive vs list price.</p>
      <a href="https://www.redwoodoutdoors.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored" class="inline-block mt-3 bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white font-semibold px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg transition-colors text-sm">Shop Redwood Outdoors ($250 Off)</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">Is Redwood Outdoors a good sauna brand?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Yes — quality build, Thermowood differentiator, US support. Main limitation is the 1-year warranty and premium price.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">How much does a Redwood Outdoors sauna cost?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Cedar barrels from ~$3,500. Thermowood models from ~$6,600. Add $800-$2,000 for shipping and electrical.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-1">What is Thermowood?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-700">Heat-treated Scandinavian wood that is more rot-resistant and dimensionally stable than standard cedar. Better for outdoor installations in wet climates.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 mt-10">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-2">Related</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/brands/almost-heaven-sauna-review" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Almost Heaven Sauna Review</a></li>
        <li><a href="/brands/dundalk-leisurecraft-review" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Dundalk LeisureCraft Review</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/best-barrel-sauna-kits" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Best Barrel Sauna Kits</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/outdoor-sauna-buying-checklist" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Outdoor Sauna Buying Checklist</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/cedar-vs-hemlock-sauna" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Cedar vs Hemlock Sauna</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
